### Module 6 — Sequelize + PostgreSQL
### Start the DB first: docker compose up -d

@base = http://localhost:3000

# ─── USERS ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a user
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "James", "email": "james@example.com" }

### Create another user
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Alice", "email": "alice@example.com" }

### Duplicate email → 409 Conflict
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "James2", "email": "james@example.com" }

### List all users
GET {{base}}/users

### Get user with their posts (note the JOIN in the SQL log)
GET {{base}}/users/1


# ─── POSTS ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a post (use a userId from above)
POST {{base}}/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My First DB Post",
  "body": "This is stored in PostgreSQL now, not memory.",
  "tags": ["database", "sequelize"],
  "published": true,
  "userId": 1
}

### Create another post
POST {{base}}/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Draft Post",
  "body": "Not published yet, working on this one.",
  "tags": ["wip"],
  "published": false,
  "userId": 1
}

### List all posts (watch the SQL in the terminal)
GET {{base}}/posts

### Filter by published
GET {{base}}/posts?published=true

### Paginate
GET {{base}}/posts?page=1&limit=1

### Get one post (includes user info via JOIN)
GET {{base}}/posts/1

### Search
GET {{base}}/posts/search?q=database

### Partial update (PATCH)
PATCH {{base}}/posts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{ "published": true }

### Delete
DELETE {{base}}/posts/2

# ─── TRANSACTION ────────────────────────────────────────

### Create user + post atomically
POST {{base}}/posts/with-user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "Bob",
  "userEmail": "bob@example.com",
  "title": "Bob's First Post",
  "body": "Created together with my user in a single transaction."
}
